article.headline: Central Florida 66, Houston 56
article.story: HOUSTON (AP) -- Anthony Williams scored 25 points and led the Golden Knights defensive effort with five blocked shots as Central Florida beat Houston 66-56 on Saturday night. Justin Rose scored 11 points and pulled down 14 rebounds for UCF (7-7, 1-1 Conference USA). Ramon Dyer lead all Houston scorers with 18 points. Brian Latham came off the bench to add 11. Houston (9-5, 0-2) was 10-of-20 from the free-throw line. UCF lead 36-29 at the half.
